        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer467405329" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7913722104968171292">Another reason why am not keen on reading best-sellers.<br/>And the fact that this book reached it&apos;s 30 print, is just ridiculous!<br/><br/>It&apos;s an OKAY book. Even though the author is talking about society pressure and how the Arabic culture is flawed by others stereotyping others, I can&apos;t but stop and laugh at the irony that this book, resembles everything negative he tried to speak out to the people about.<br/><br/>But to be fair, Yasser Harb did have a solid opinion about various issues which I myself suffer from wh</span>
  <span id="freeText7913722104968171292" style="display:none">Another reason why am not keen on reading best-sellers.<br />And the fact that this book reached it's 30 print, is just ridiculous!<br /><br />It's an OKAY book. Even though the author is talking about society pressure and how the Arabic culture is flawed by others stereotyping others, I can't but stop and laugh at the irony that this book, resembles everything negative he tried to speak out to the people about.<br /><br />But to be fair, Yasser Harb did have a solid opinion about various issues which I myself suffer from while dealing with Middle Eastern. There were few good chapters that I found myself giving a damn about. Yet there were some articles that are very WRONG, at least to me.. the general idea of the articles, I get where he is going but the points and examples he use to convince the reader are just catastrophic! They are very controversial that I kept on convincing myself to calm down, stop with the counter-attack and just read the guy out!<br /><br />I think I might be harsh when I say that this book will work only on the actual type of people who he is talking about, but it's the truth. <br /><br />Yet I think that it's a good thing to have such a book available for those who need it. Like I could now just highlight some chapters and give it to the person I think the chapters belongs to them and hope they will get the message.<br /><br />All I can say is that it's not my cup of tea.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="7913722104968171292" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
