<div id="review_3763582880" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3763582880" />
    <a title="Hadeel Ghazi" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/23538770-hadeel-ghazi"><img alt="Hadeel Ghazi" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1377905980p2/23538770.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3763582880?book_show_action=true">Jan 10, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Hadeel Ghazi" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Hadeel Ghazi" href="/user/show/23538770-hadeel-ghazi">Hadeel Ghazi</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3763582880" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8147033841607488165">ونرجع لنفس الدوامة لكتب ال<br/>self help <br/>وكتب التنمية البشرية الي كلها تشبه بعضها .. <br/><br/>I couldn&apos;t relate to the Mecca and Haj parts.<br/>And him describing Darwin&apos;s theory of evolution and natural selection as &quot;mythical&quot; just pissed me off..<br/>I have also found some parts of this book to be offensive, Arabs are not all that bad you know. We have great Arab thinkers, scientists and mathematicians. We&apos;re not all dumb and indecisive! <br/>Bringing up the topic of &quot;America&apos;s got talent&quot; and how the western societies ar</span>
  <span id="freeText8147033841607488165" style="display:none">ونرجع لنفس الدوامة لكتب ال<br />self help <br />وكتب التنمية البشرية الي كلها تشبه بعضها .. <br /><br />I couldn't relate to the Mecca and Haj parts.<br />And him describing Darwin's theory of evolution and natural selection as "mythical" just pissed me off..<br />I have also found some parts of this book to be offensive, Arabs are not all that bad you know. We have great Arab thinkers, scientists and mathematicians. We're not all dumb and indecisive! <br />Bringing up the topic of "America's got talent" and how the western societies are supportive of their talents and how they let people become whoever they want to be, was really unnecessary. <br />We have talents, we have singers and song writers, artists who are still singing and bringing joy and happiness to the world. We have musicians and composers of all of the Arab countries who are practicing and doing what they love and nobody is trying to stop them from doing that. <br /><br />I don't know, it was a nice and light read but overall, neither educational nor inspiring.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8147033841607488165" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


