  <span id="freeText15337984906636502813" style="display:none">I'm going to write this in English as I'm better in it than Arabic.<br /><br />First of all, the reason why I picked up this book in the first place was for pure Arabic enhancement that I need. My friend suggested me this book because it was an "easy read".<br /><br />I must say, out of all the Arabic books I tried reading, this was the only one that kept me interested in reading more. I finished it faster than I expected. <br /><br />I agree with most of his statements and like how he delivered his views in different aspects of life and the society. Although a few chapters didn't really make me go "wow, spot on Yasser" but most of it kept me thinking, 'so true, I didn't openly "notice" it till now'. <br /><br />Another thing that I didn't like was, why make more than 4 publish of the same book when it's already good? My friend read الطبعة الحادي عشر and said that it was unorganised and that a few of the chapters from the copy I was reading which was the fourth publish, hadn't been on her copy. </span>
