<span id="freeTextContainer4441591454051242999">I thought it was an inspiring read + gives hope to a better society not only for the Arab nations but also to a better world. <br/><br/>I honestly was unable to see the analogy between Starbucks and Picasso... Given the simplicity of language and somewhat of a depth analysis of societal issues. I liked the way the book was structured as it can be a book on the go for quick reads on each topic. I did find though there were some extensively long sentences that bothered me. Shorter sentences would have made </span>
  <span id="freeText4441591454051242999" style="display:none">I thought it was an inspiring read + gives hope to a better society not only for the Arab nations but also to a better world. <br /><br />I honestly was unable to see the analogy between Starbucks and Picasso... Given the simplicity of language and somewhat of a depth analysis of societal issues. I liked the way the book was structured as it can be a book on the go for quick reads on each topic. I did find though there were some extensively long sentences that bothered me. Shorter sentences would have made it more clear and to the point. Although some topics were a bit off for me, as I did not see the complete relevance. I think it was an attempt at creativity. <br /><br />Overall, I enjoyed reading this book! I applaud the author for drawing similarities between cultures and faiths. <br /><br />:') <br /><br /></span>
